1
00:00:03,639 --> 00:00:06,153
l was unstoppable. I mean, I was on fire.

2
00:00:06,319 --> 00:00:09,516
It was like my mind and my body
were totally connected.

3
00:00:09,680 --> 00:00:13,514
Like athletes must feel
when they're in the zone.

4
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:16,638
PENNY:
Again, it was miniature golf.

5
00:00:17,480 --> 00:00:19,550
Admit it, you're a little turned on.

6
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:21,278
You can't be this proud.

7
00:00:21,439 --> 00:00:24,875
-Why not?
-Because I beat you.

8
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:27,875
-Hey.
-Hi.

9
00:00:28,039 --> 00:00:29,518
Oh, good, you're back.

10
00:00:29,679 --> 00:00:33,115
We have some exciting news.

11
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,079
Okay.

12
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:38,710
As you know, Amy and l
have been together a long time...

13
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:42,395
...and a lot of things
I never thought possible...

14
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:44,198
...now seem possible.

15
00:00:45,039 --> 00:00:46,916
Okay.

16
00:00:47,639 --> 00:00:50,199
After a careful evaluation
of our relationship...

17
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:54,757
...we decided that the time was right
to take a step forward.

18
00:01:00,159 --> 00:01:02,036
Okay.

19
00:01:03,639 --> 00:01:05,118
Do you wanna say it?

20
00:01:05,279 --> 00:01:07,315
Let's say it together.

21
00:01:07,479 --> 00:01:10,312
-We're getting a turtle.
-We're getting a turtle.

22
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:17,193
See, this is why I've been saying
we should keep champagne on ice.

23
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:19,557
-Sarcasm?
-Yes.

24
00:01:19,719 --> 00:01:22,870
That was tricky, because when it comes
to alcohol, she means business.

25
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:26,797
-Well, we're very happy for you.
-Yes.

26
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:31,033
Thank you.
Acquiring ajoint pet is a big step for us.

27
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,078
No, it's true. It means that
we care so much about each other...

28
00:01:34,239 --> 00:01:36,878
...there's enough left over
for an 8-ounce reptile.

29
00:01:38,159 --> 00:01:39,308
Why a turtle?

30
00:01:39,479 --> 00:01:42,596
Well, after much deliberation,
we've determined that a turtle...

31
00:01:42,759 --> 00:01:43,987
...is the ideal pet.

32
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:47,152
They don't shed fur, they don't make noise....

33
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:49,880
For Halloween,
we can dress him as a cobblestone.

34
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:54,391
And if he ever goes berserk,
I know I can outrun him.

35
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:57,711
Coincidentally, that's also
why I chose you as a roommate.

36
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,868
Well, congratulations.

37
00:02:00,039 --> 00:02:03,349
Who would've thought you would be
the first in our group to start a family?

38
00:02:04,239 --> 00:02:06,673
That's what I said.

39
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:33,592
So where's your roommate tonight?

40
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:36,593
Well, I thought it was a little unfair
that she's always here...

41
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:38,876
...and you never get a chance
to stay over...

42
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:40,951
...so I killed her.

43
00:02:42,799 --> 00:02:43,993
Remember our agreement.

44
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:49,154
You can joke about murdering people,
but you have to say "just kidding."

45
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:53,313
And the more important thing to remember
is that I'd never hurt you.

46
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:58,758
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

47
00:02:59,559 --> 00:03:00,708
Oh, crap.

48
00:03:01,079 --> 00:03:03,639
l have to run over to the hospital
and check on a patient.

49
00:03:03,999 --> 00:03:07,196
-That's okay. I can come back later.
-No, no, don't be silly.

50
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:08,998
I won't be gone long. Just stay here.

51
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:13,149
Okay, cool. You're sure your roommate's
not gonna come back while I'm here alone?

52
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:14,833
Because that would be awkward.

53
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,275
-Don't worry, she's in Palm Springs.
-Oh, good.

54
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:19,510
Well, her torso is.

55
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:22,154
Just kidding.

56
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:25,238
I put her in awood chipper.

57
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:30,875
Oh, dear Lord. Oh, dear Lord.

58
00:03:31,039 --> 00:03:32,631
It's okay.

59
00:03:32,799 --> 00:03:36,428
-You made it, we're fine.
-That was a lot of puppies.

60
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:42,076
Let's forget about them
and pick ourselves out a nice turtle.

61
00:03:42,279 --> 00:03:44,315
Oh, how about this one up on the log?

62
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:46,072
Oh, I don't know.

63
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:47,829
He looks like ajerk.

64
00:03:50,840 --> 00:03:52,159
How about this one?

65
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:54,550
He's barely moving. He looks half dead.

66
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:56,995
I know. I like him too.

67
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:00,788
Hi, little guy.

68
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:03,670
How'd you like to come home with us?

69
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:07,310
You'll be living with me,
because we don't live in the same house.

70
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:08,674
But that's not your fault.

71
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:11,912
Like you, we're taking it ridiculously slow.

72
00:04:14,279 --> 00:04:17,954
You'll stay with me when he's at Comic-Con,
or away for work.

73
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:22,398
Yeah, or if they accept
Daddy's application to live on Mars.

74
00:04:23,520 --> 00:04:25,272
What are you talking about?

75
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:28,910
Well, there's this company that's attempting
to establish a colony on Mars...

76
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:31,071
...and I applied to be among the first to go.

77
00:04:31,239 --> 00:04:32,752
What should we name him?

78
00:04:33,119 --> 00:04:36,634
You know, I came in thinking "Seth"...

79
00:04:37,160 --> 00:04:39,674
...but he kind of looks Italian.

80
00:04:40,479 --> 00:04:43,789
You applied for a mission
to be a colonist on another planet...

81
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:45,916
...and couldn't be bothered to tell me?

82
00:04:47,919 --> 00:04:49,398
Would you have approved?

83
00:04:49,560 --> 00:04:50,754
Of course not.

84
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:54,596
Well, based on your reaction,
it looks like I made the right choice.

85
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:57,559
Isn't that right, Giuseppe?

86
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:03,638
Hey. Hey.

87
00:05:03,799 --> 00:05:06,393
Listen, I have a little confession to make.

88
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:09,074
Aw. Is this your first time?

89
00:05:11,599 --> 00:05:15,717
No, I got you something for Valentine's Day,
and l was too embarrassed to give it to you.

90
00:05:15,879 --> 00:05:17,153
Well, why?

91
00:05:17,319 --> 00:05:21,073
Because I got it at the dirty store.

92
00:05:21,879 --> 00:05:24,598
You went to the dirty store without me?

93
00:05:25,879 --> 00:05:28,552
In sunglasses and a hat
after I parked two blocks away.

94
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,756
-Well, get it. Get it for me.
-Yeah?

95
00:05:30,919 --> 00:05:33,274
-Yeah.
-Okay. Uh, well, I hope it's fun.

96
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:37,558
It comes with paints
and it's kind of creative and artistic.

97
00:05:37,919 --> 00:05:40,797
Okay, did you go to the dirty store,
or Michaels?

98
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:45,430
No, no, we cover ourselves in body paint...

99
00:05:45,599 --> 00:05:48,989
...and then we get on this big canvas
and do our thing.

100
00:05:49,799 --> 00:05:54,429
Whoa. It's kind of a big step for a guy
who only recently agreed to take his socks off.

101
00:05:55,279 --> 00:05:57,952
-You're making fun of me. Forget it.
-No. No, I wanna do it.

102
00:05:58,120 --> 00:05:59,235
-Really?
-Yeah.

103
00:05:59,399 --> 00:06:02,948
Let's you, me and your very, very pale feet
make some art.

104
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:04,109
[LEONARD CHUCKLES]

105
00:06:04,279 --> 00:06:06,668
When you go back to the store,
I wanna go with you.

106
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:10,355
Okay. But it's a drive.
The one I went to is in San Diego.

107
00:06:12,479 --> 00:06:15,437
-How are the taxes going?
-Okay.

108
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:18,637
But you got a lot of receipts
for the Lego Store in here.

109
00:06:20,279 --> 00:06:23,396
Those are business expenses.
You can write those off.

110
00:06:24,559 --> 00:06:28,313
A $200 R2-D2 is a business expense?

111
00:06:28,959 --> 00:06:33,157
Oh, Bernie, you're gonna have to sound
a lot more confident when we get audited.

112
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:36,639
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

113
00:06:38,239 --> 00:06:39,592
Hey. What's up?

114
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,629
Oh, Emily ran back to the hospital,
so I'm just hanging out at her place.

115
00:06:43,799 --> 00:06:46,996
-What are you, uh--? What are you doing?
-Just playing video games...

116
00:06:47,159 --> 00:06:48,751
...while Bernie does the taxes.

117
00:06:48,919 --> 00:06:51,069
What are you, a little kid?

118
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:54,038
Is she gonna cut your dinner
into little pieces too?

119
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:58,354
She doesn't have to,
I filled up on jelly beans.

120
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:01,709
So, uh, what game are you--?

121
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:04,155
Oh, crap.

122
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,673
-What's wrong?
-I can't get Emily's nightstand to close.

123
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:10,433
-So?
-She's gonna know I was looking in it.

124
00:07:10,639 --> 00:07:12,516
Why were you looking in it?

125
00:07:12,679 --> 00:07:16,433
Well, there's a question I better have
a good answer to before she gets back.

126
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,637
Okay, calm down.
There's probably something jammed behind it.

127
00:07:19,799 --> 00:07:21,949
-Just pull it out and see what's there.
-Hang on.

128
00:07:26,559 --> 00:07:28,436
Oh, no. Oh, no.

129
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,556
Oh, God, no.

130
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:34,511
You know what? You sound busy.
I'm gonna let you go.

131
00:07:34,919 --> 00:07:37,991
Dude, the whole front came off.
Now, she's gonna know I was snooping.

132
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,229
What's happening?

133
00:07:39,439 --> 00:07:42,158
Raj was snooping through
Emily's drawers and broke one.

134
00:07:42,839 --> 00:07:45,911
Aw. I'm gonna miss her.

135
00:07:48,159 --> 00:07:49,478
So, what do you think?

136
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:53,759
I thought it'd be a little more....

137
00:07:53,919 --> 00:07:55,796
Just more.

138
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:01,315
I'm not even sure
why we were out of breath.

139
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:05,754
I mean, did we move at all?

140
00:08:06,559 --> 00:08:07,992
Maybe along the Z axis...

141
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:11,357
...but X and Y are looking pretty sad.

142
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:15,709
Come on, we are not old, boring people.
We could do better than this.

143
00:08:15,919 --> 00:08:18,149
That's true.
How late did we stay up last night?

144
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:20,756
Almost 1 am.

145
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:23,755
Damn straight, almost 1 am.

146
00:08:25,799 --> 00:08:30,031
And we weren't even watching TV,
we were watching Netflix like the kids do.

147
00:08:30,519 --> 00:08:34,034
Yeah. Is it a comedy? Is it a drama?
Nobody knows.

148
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,713
Come on. We are gonna do this.

149
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:41,158
You get the paint, I'll rest for 30 to 40 minutes,
and then we do this.

150
00:08:42,879 --> 00:08:47,873
I can't believe you almost had me
bring awild animal into my home.

151
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:50,315
No one told you to poke the turtle's face.

152
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:53,999
l was playing Got Your Nose.

153
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:57,713
That's how you get children to like you.

154
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,631
I'm surprised you care if he likes you...

155
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:03,598
...since you're leaving the planet
the first chance you get.

156
00:09:03,759 --> 00:09:07,513
This again. Amy, I've already had
one new hole torn in my body today...

157
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:10,148
...I don't need another one.

158
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:14,872
Sheldon, I know the odds of you
even going to Mars are incredibly small...

159
00:09:15,039 --> 00:09:17,599
...but it hurts that you would volunteer
for something...

160
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:19,716
...that would take you away from me forever.

161
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,033
You wouldn't leave me...

162
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:25,556
...for the chance to be one of the first humans
to colonize another planet?

163
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:29,235
I would at least mention it
before filling out the application.

164
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:33,598
Huh. That's exactly what Leonard, Wolowitz,
Koothrappali, Bernadette and Penny said.

165
00:09:35,519 --> 00:09:38,556
And who says you could even survive
an interplanetary mission anyway?

166
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,790
You could barely survive a tiny turtle bite.

167
00:09:41,399 --> 00:09:42,878
First of all, this...

168
00:09:43,039 --> 00:09:45,553
...has only made me stronger.

169
00:09:45,719 --> 00:09:48,756
But beyond that,
all I did was fill out an application.

170
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:52,876
You know what? Go to Mars, Sheldon.

171
00:09:55,839 --> 00:09:57,875
Is there anything I can do to cheer you up?

172
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:59,189
No, forget it.

173
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:03,511
-What if I play the Star Trek theme on my nose?
-Please don't.

174
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:06,474
[HUMMING "STAR TREKII THEME
THROUGH NOSE]

175
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:12,873
Yep, you're mad.

176
00:10:18,319 --> 00:10:20,879
-Okay, let me see the damage.
RAJ: Hang on.

177
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:24,113
I think you broke the dowels.

178
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:26,714
You won't have time to glue it.
You'll have to nail it.

179
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:30,356
-With what?
-Does she have any pillows or wine glasses?

180
00:10:31,159 --> 00:10:32,478
-She does.
-Great.

181
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:35,069
Neither of those. Try a hammer!

182
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:40,958
Did that feel good?
You feel like a big man now?

183
00:10:44,800 --> 00:10:47,360
l was going to make you Red Zinger...

184
00:10:47,560 --> 00:10:52,350
...but since Mars is the red planet,
I went with peppermint.

185
00:10:54,879 --> 00:10:56,517
Why do you even wanna do this?

186
00:10:57,919 --> 00:10:59,557
Actually...

187
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:04,157
...as part of the application,
I was required to make a short video...

188
00:11:04,319 --> 00:11:06,275
...answering that very question.

189
00:11:06,999 --> 00:11:09,149
-You wanna see it?
-Can't you just tell me?

190
00:11:09,599 --> 00:11:11,635
But I made a video.

191
00:11:13,759 --> 00:11:15,431
SHELDON [ON VIDEO]:
I'm Dr. Sheldon Cooper...

192
00:11:15,879 --> 00:11:19,428
...and I'd like to tell you
whylshould be chosen to...

193
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:22,515
[ECHOES]
...go to Mars!

194
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:27,037
I'm exceedingly smart.
I graduated college at 14.

195
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:31,079
While my brother was getting an STD,
I was getting a PhD.

196
00:11:33,639 --> 00:11:35,994
Penicillin can't take this away.

197
00:11:36,999 --> 00:11:40,389
Being in close quarters,
cleanliness is important.

198
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:43,438
And my hygiene is impeccable.

199
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,556
In fact, animals don't trust me...

200
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:48,188
...because I smell like nothing.

201
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:49,429
[SNIFFS]

202
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:51,192
Literally nothing.

203
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:56,913
During the seven-month space ﬂight,
I can keep up morale...

204
00:11:57,079 --> 00:11:59,354
...with my wacky sense of humor.

205
00:12:01,759 --> 00:12:02,714
Hey, Leonard...

206
00:12:02,919 --> 00:12:05,752
...is there any peanut brittle left in that can?

207
00:12:05,919 --> 00:12:08,638
You mean this weirdly suspicious one?

208
00:12:08,799 --> 00:12:11,632
Yes. Open it and check.

209
00:12:16,639 --> 00:12:19,199
I don't get it. There's actually peanut brittle--

210
00:12:25,999 --> 00:12:28,115
Please go to Mars.

211
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:31,153
But on a more serious note...

212
00:12:31,319 --> 00:12:33,674
...the most important reason
lwanna go to Mars...

213
00:12:33,839 --> 00:12:36,228
...is thatlbelieve, as a scientist...

214
00:12:36,399 --> 00:12:40,790
...it's my duty to push the boundaries
of human knowledge forward.

215
00:12:40,959 --> 00:12:43,837
Now, lknow that life on Mars will be difﬁcult.

216
00:12:43,999 --> 00:12:46,672
But life here on Earth is no picnic.

217
00:12:46,839 --> 00:12:48,431
Also, picnics are no picnic.

218
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:53,312
"Where should we go for lunch?
Oh, lknow, the ground. "

219
00:12:54,800 --> 00:12:57,234
In conclusion,
thank you for considering me...

220
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:59,994
...for this journey of a lifetime.

221
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:04,160
[ECHOES]
To Mars.

222
00:13:06,080 --> 00:13:10,119
Afterwards, Leonard blew his nose
and pie came out.

223
00:13:13,599 --> 00:13:15,317
LEONARD:
Right there.

224
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:17,357
Right there. Oh, God, that's it.

225
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:25,271
-How did you get paint in your eye?
-You wouldn't let me wear safety goggles.

226
00:13:30,280 --> 00:13:32,475
This looks terrible. She-- She's gonna know.

227
00:13:32,639 --> 00:13:34,994
It's ﬁne. You just need two more nails.

228
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:38,277
-Okay, where should I put them?
-In Emily's eyes.

229
00:13:39,879 --> 00:13:41,232
You're not helping.

230
00:13:41,760 --> 00:13:43,796
Well, maybe this is what you get
for snooping.

231
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:45,916
-lt's bad enough that l have to deal--
EMILY: Raj?

232
00:13:46,079 --> 00:13:48,912
-l'm back.
-Oh, no.

233
00:13:49,879 --> 00:13:51,198
-Hey.
-Hi.

234
00:13:51,999 --> 00:13:54,354
How--? How's the hospital?

235
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:57,274
Fine. What were you doing in there?

236
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:00,791
Uh, we-- Well....

237
00:14:02,199 --> 00:14:05,828
Look, I don't wanna lie to you.
I got curious, I was looking around...

238
00:14:05,999 --> 00:14:08,149
...and I broke the drawer on your nightstand.

239
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:11,280
-You were looking in my nightstand?
-Yeah.

240
00:14:11,599 --> 00:14:14,830
So the first time I leave you alone,
you snoop on me?

241
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:18,354
-You've never snooped around my apartment?
-No.

242
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:22,596
Come on, think back.
It would really help if you had.

243
00:14:24,079 --> 00:14:26,991
EMILY: I can't believe you don't trust me.
-She sounds really mad.

244
00:14:28,959 --> 00:14:31,951
-We should hang up.
-Yeah, we should.

245
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:34,873
-But we're not going to, are we?
-Not a chance.

246
00:14:36,079 --> 00:14:38,388
What happened to "snooping is wrong"?

247
00:14:38,560 --> 00:14:41,711
Oh, we're already going to jail for tax fraud.
Who cares?

248
00:14:44,319 --> 00:14:46,355
Well, we did it.

249
00:14:46,679 --> 00:14:48,112
We sure did.

250
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:49,872
I mean, I was on fire.

251
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:52,156
l was in the zone like an athlete.

252
00:14:52,560 --> 00:14:54,596
Sweetie, I beat you at this too.

253
00:14:55,720 --> 00:14:57,073
So where do we wanna hang it?

254
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:59,310
What, are you kidding?
We're not hanging it.

255
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:01,277
But it's an expression of our love.

256
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:03,630
And our butts. Not hanging it.

257
00:15:05,079 --> 00:15:06,990
Seems a shame to throw it away.

258
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:08,959
Yeah.

259
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:13,591
Oh. We can give it to Sheldon
and tell him William Shatner painted it.

260
00:15:15,999 --> 00:15:18,354
God, I love you. I love you so much.

261
00:15:21,279 --> 00:15:23,156
I think I'm gonna go home.

262
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:25,832
Why?

263
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:28,949
I really don't understand
what's happening here.

264
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:31,793
You know, Sheldon, at any other time...

265
00:15:31,959 --> 00:15:35,474
...learning that you had plans to go live
on Mars would be a slow news day.

266
00:15:35,999 --> 00:15:39,594
But a couple of hours ago,
we were getting a turtle.

267
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:42,069
And silly as it sounds...

268
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:44,748
...I thought that meant something.

269
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:47,512
Amy.

270
00:15:48,159 --> 00:15:50,229
Why didn't I give her Sleepytime tea?

271
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:54,069
Amy, wait.

272
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:57,038
Getting a turtle meant a great deal to me too.

273
00:15:57,199 --> 00:15:59,759
Sure. Unless something better comes along.

274
00:16:01,079 --> 00:16:03,274
Do you want me to withdraw my application?

275
00:16:04,759 --> 00:16:08,798
What I want is for us to be
planning our future together.

276
00:16:10,719 --> 00:16:13,108
And in that future...

277
00:16:13,279 --> 00:16:14,917
...are we on the same planet?

278
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:19,118
Because I've seen people
make the long-distance thing work.

279
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:20,793
-We're on the same planet!
-Okay.

280
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:26,631
Does that planet have to be Earth?

281
00:16:28,319 --> 00:16:30,116
Are you asking me to go to Mars with you?

282
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:31,635


283
00:16:32,319 --> 00:16:35,629
Yeah, if I'm going to a barren,
lifeless environment...

284
00:16:35,799 --> 00:16:39,838
...where the chances of survival
are slim to none...

285
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:41,433
...I want you there with me.

286
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:50,028
Why don't we go back to the apartment
and fill out your application?

287
00:16:50,560 --> 00:16:52,198
Okay.

288
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:56,000
I suppose being the first people
on a new planet...

289
00:16:56,160 --> 00:16:57,593
...would be incredibly exciting.

290
00:16:58,079 --> 00:16:59,478
I know.

291
00:16:59,639 --> 00:17:02,870
We could be the first
to plant a flag on Mars.

292
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:06,350
We could be the first
to watch Mars Attacks! on Mars.

293
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:08,514
We could be the first to say:

294
00:17:08,679 --> 00:17:11,591
"Good Lord.
What on Mars are you talking about?"

295
00:17:12,959 --> 00:17:18,079
You know, we could also be
the first people to procreate on Mars.

296
00:17:19,799 --> 00:17:22,711
You just can't keep it in your space pants,
can you?

297
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:28,918
Think about it. If we had a family there,
our kids would be Martians.

298
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:33,553
They would, wouldn't they?

299
00:17:34,359 --> 00:17:36,589
We could give them cool Martian names...

300
00:17:36,759 --> 00:17:38,909
...and we could teach them
about Martian history.

301
00:17:39,079 --> 00:17:40,717
Like, "Who planted those flags?"

302
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:44,589
And, uh, "Where'd that copy
of Mars Attacks! come from?"

303
00:17:45,279 --> 00:17:48,032
I guess we'll have to make
a new video together as a couple.

304
00:17:48,799 --> 00:17:51,313
Good idea. Yeah--

305
00:17:51,839 --> 00:17:54,034
And since you've had such a rough day...

306
00:17:54,199 --> 00:17:56,508
...l'm gonna let you throw the pie
in Leonard's face.

307
00:18:03,319 --> 00:18:05,992
-Thank you for forgiving me.
-lt's okay.

308
00:18:06,159 --> 00:18:08,548
At some point,
we were bound to have our first fight.

309
00:18:09,039 --> 00:18:13,317
Well, it almost happened
when you called my apple-pie crust doughy.

310
00:18:15,479 --> 00:18:18,869
The truth is you were right,
and l was just angry at myself.

311
00:18:20,080 --> 00:18:21,911
Can I ask you one thing?

312
00:18:22,079 --> 00:18:23,228
Of course. What?

313
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,752
Did you look in my closet?

314
00:18:26,760 --> 00:18:29,638
-No, just the drawer.
-You promise you didn't look in the closet?

315
00:18:29,799 --> 00:18:31,994
I promise. Why, what's in there?

316
00:18:32,159 --> 00:18:33,990
sDon't worry about it.

317
00:18:34,559 --> 00:18:36,038
Good night.

